msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 29"
msgstr "Long Discourses 29"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn29:2.1"
msgid "Pāsādikasutta"
msgstr "An Impressive Discourse"

#. </h1></div><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts3.117"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:3.1"
msgid "<span class=\"evam\">Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​</span>"
msgstr "<span class=”evam”>So I have heard.</span>"

msgctxt "dn29:3.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati vedhaññā nāma sakyā, tesaṃ ambavane "
"pāsāde."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans in a stilt "
"longhouse in a mango grove belonging to the Sakyan family named Vedhañña."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.118"></a>
#. VAR: nāṭaputto → nātaputto (bj) | nāthaputto (pts1)
msgctxt "dn29:4.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto pāvāyaṃ adhunākālaṅkato hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta had recently passed away at Pāvā."

msgctxt "dn29:4.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa kālaṃkiriyāya bhinnā nigaṇṭhā dvedhikajātā bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā "
"vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharanti:"
msgstr ""
"With his passing the Jain ascetics split, dividing into two factions, "
"arguing, quarreling, and fighting, continually wounding each other with "
"barbed words:"

msgctxt "dn29:4.3"
msgid ""
"“na tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāsi, ahaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāmi, kiṃ "
"tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānissasi?"
msgstr ""
"“You don’t understand this teaching and training. I understand this teaching "
"and training. What, you understand this teaching and training?"

msgctxt "dn29:4.4"
msgid "Micchāpaṭipanno tvamasi, ahamasmi sammāpaṭipanno."
msgstr "You’re practicing wrong. I’m practicing right."

msgctxt "dn29:4.5"
msgid "Sahitaṃ me, asahitaṃ te."
msgstr "I stay on topic, you don’t."

msgctxt "dn29:4.6"
msgid "Purevacanīyaṃ pacchā avaca, pacchāvacanīyaṃ pure avaca."
msgstr ""
"You said last what you should have said first. You said first what you "
"should have said last."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn29:4.7"
msgid ""
"Adhiciṇṇaṃ te viparāvattaṃ, āropito te vādo, niggahito tvamasi, cara "
"vādappamokkhāya, nibbeṭhehi vā sace pahosī”ti."
msgstr ""
"What you’ve thought so much about has been disproved. Your doctrine is "
"refuted. Go on, save your doctrine! You’re trapped; get yourself out of this—"
"if you can!”"

#. VAR: Vadhoyeva kho → vadhoyeveko (mr)
#. VAR: vattati → anuvattati (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn29:4.8"
msgid "Vadhoyeva kho maññe nigaṇṭhesu nāṭaputtiyesu vattati."
msgstr ""
"You’d think there was nothing but slaughter going on among the Jain ascetics."

#. VAR: tepi → te tesu (mr)
#. VAR: nibbinnarūpā → nibiṇṇarūpā (pts1) | nibbindarūpā (mr)
msgctxt "dn29:4.9"
msgid ""
"Yepi nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa sāvakā gihī odātavasanā, tepi nigaṇṭhesu "
"nāṭaputtiyesu nibbinnarūpā virattarūpā paṭivānarūpā, yathā taṃ durakkhāte "
"dhammavinaye duppavedite aniyyānike anupasamasaṃvattanike "
"asammāsambuddhappavedite bhinnathūpe appaṭisaraṇe."
msgstr ""
"And the Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta’s white-clothed lay disciples were disillusioned, "
"dismayed, and disappointed in the Jain ascetics. They were equally "
"disappointed with a teaching and training so poorly explained and poorly "
"propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, announced by someone who "
"is not a fully awakened Buddha, with broken monument and without a refuge."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3"></a>
#. VAR: vassaṃvuṭṭho → vassaṃ vuttho (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn29:5.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho cundo samaṇuddeso pāvāyaṃ vassaṃvuṭṭho yena sāmagāmo, yenāyasmā "
"ānando tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"And then, after completing the rainy season residence near Pāvā, the novice "
"Cunda went to see Venerable Ānanda at Sāma village."

msgctxt "dn29:5.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "He bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "dn29:5.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho cundo samaṇuddeso āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and told him what had happened."

msgctxt "dn29:5.4"
msgid "“nigaṇṭho, bhante, nāṭaputto pāvāyaṃ adhunākālaṅkato."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:5.5"
msgid "Tassa kālaṃkiriyāya bhinnā nigaṇṭhā dvedhikajātā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:5.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:5.7"
msgid "bhinnathūpe appaṭisaraṇe”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:6.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando cundaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Ānanda said to him:"

msgctxt "dn29:6.2"
msgid "“atthi kho idaṃ, āvuso cunda, kathāpābhataṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya."
msgstr "“Reverend Cunda, we should see the Buddha about this matter."

msgctxt "dn29:6.3"
msgid "Āyāmāvuso cunda, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamissāma;"
msgstr "Come, let’s go to the Buddha "

#. VAR: bhagavato ārocessāmā”ti → āroceyyāmāti (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn29:6.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ bhagavato ārocessāmā”ti."
msgstr "and tell him about this.”"

msgctxt "dn29:6.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho cundo samaṇuddeso āyasmato ānandassa paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Cunda."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ca ānando cundo ca samaṇuddeso yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "Then Ānanda and Cunda went to the Buddha,"

msgctxt "dn29:7.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "dn29:7.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and told him what had happened."

msgctxt "dn29:7.4"
msgid ""
"“ayaṃ, bhante, cundo samaṇuddeso evamāha, ‘nigaṇṭho, bhante, nāṭaputto "
"pāvāyaṃ adhunākālaṅkato, tassa kālaṅkiriyāya bhinnā nigaṇṭhā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:7.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:7.6"
msgid "bhinnathūpe appaṭisaraṇe’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:8.1"
msgid "1. Asammāsambuddhappaveditadhammavinaya"
msgstr "The Teaching of the Unawakened"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.119"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ hetaṃ, cunda, hoti durakkhāte dhammavinaye duppavedite aniyyānike "
"anupasamasaṃvattanike asammāsambuddhappavedite."
msgstr ""
"“That’s what happens, Cunda, when a teaching and training is poorly "
"explained and poorly propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, "
"announced by someone who is not a fully awakened Buddha."

msgctxt "dn29:9.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, cunda, satthā ca hoti asammāsambuddho, dhammo ca durakkhāto "
"duppavedito aniyyāniko anupasamasaṃvattaniko asammāsambuddhappavedito, "
"sāvako ca tasmiṃ dhamme na dhammānudhammappaṭipanno viharati na "
"sāmīcippaṭipanno na anudhammacārī, vokkamma ca tamhā dhammā vattati."
msgstr ""
"Take the case where a teacher is not awakened, and the teaching is poorly "
"explained and poorly propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, "
"announced by someone who is not a fully awakened Buddha. A disciple in that "
"teaching does not practice in line with the teachings, does not practice "
"following that procedure, does not live in line with the teaching. They "
"proceed having turned away from that teaching."

msgctxt "dn29:9.3"
msgid "So evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr "You should say this to them:"

msgctxt "dn29:9.4"
msgid ""
"‘tassa te, āvuso, lābhā, tassa te suladdhaṃ, satthā ca te asammāsambuddho, "
"dhammo ca durakkhāto duppavedito aniyyāniko anupasamasaṃvattaniko "
"asammāsambuddhappavedito."
msgstr ""
"‘You’re fortunate, reverend, you’re so very fortunate! For your teacher is "
"not awakened, and their teaching is poorly explained and poorly propounded, "
"not emancipating, not leading to peace, announced by someone who is not a "
"fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "dn29:9.5"
msgid ""
"Tvañca tasmiṃ dhamme na dhammānudhammappaṭipanno viharasi, na "
"sāmīcippaṭipanno, na anudhammacārī, vokkamma ca tamhā dhammā vattasī’ti."
msgstr ""
"But you don’t practice in line with that teaching, you don’t practice "
"following that procedure, you don’t live in line with the teaching. You "
"proceed having turned away from that teaching.’"

msgctxt "dn29:9.6"
msgid ""
"Iti kho, cunda, satthāpi tattha gārayho, dhammopi tattha gārayho, sāvako ca "
"tattha evaṃ pāsaṃso."
msgstr ""
"In such a case the teacher and the teaching are to blame, but the student "
"deserves praise."

msgctxt "dn29:9.7"
msgid "Yo kho, cunda, evarūpaṃ sāvakaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Suppose someone was to say to such a disciple:"

msgctxt "dn29:9.8"
msgid ""
"‘etāyasmā tathā paṭipajjatu, yathā te satthārā dhammo desito paññatto’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Come on, venerable, practice as taught and pointed out by your teacher.’"

# Cp. AN 1.320
msgctxt "dn29:9.9"
msgid ""
"Yo ca samādapeti, yañca samādapeti, yo ca samādapito tathattāya paṭipajjati."
msgstr ""
"The one who encourages, the one who they encourage, and the one who "
"practices accordingly all make much bad karma."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn29:9.10"
msgid "Sabbe te bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavanti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:9.11"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn29:9.12"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ hetaṃ, cunda, hoti durakkhāte dhammavinaye duppavedite aniyyānike "
"anupasamasaṃvattanike asammāsambuddhappavedite."
msgstr ""
"It’s because that teaching and training is poorly explained and poorly "
"propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, announced by someone who "
"is not a fully awakened Buddha."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wp" id="wp7"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.120"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:10.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, cunda, satthā ca hoti asammāsambuddho, dhammo ca durakkhāto "
"duppavedito aniyyāniko anupasamasaṃvattaniko asammāsambuddhappavedito, "
"sāvako ca tasmiṃ dhamme dhammānudhammappaṭipanno viharati sāmīcippaṭipanno "
"anudhammacārī, samādāya taṃ dhammaṃ vattati."
msgstr ""
"Take the case where a teacher is not awakened, and the teaching is poorly "
"explained and poorly propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, "
"announced by someone who is not a fully awakened Buddha. A disciple in that "
"teaching practices in line with the teachings, practices following that "
"procedure, lives in line with the teaching. They proceed having undertaken "
"that teaching."

msgctxt "dn29:10.2"
msgid "So evamassa vacanīyo:"
msgstr "You should say this to them:"

msgctxt "dn29:10.3"
msgid ""
"‘tassa te, āvuso, alābhā, tassa te dulladdhaṃ, satthā ca te asammāsambuddho, "
"dhammo ca durakkhāto duppavedito aniyyāniko anupasamasaṃvattaniko "
"asammāsambuddhappavedito."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s your loss, reverend, it’s your misfortune! For your teacher is not "
"awakened, and their teaching is poorly explained and poorly propounded, not "
"emancipating, not leading to peace, announced by someone who is not a fully "
"awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "dn29:10.4"
msgid ""
"Tvañca tasmiṃ dhamme dhammānudhammappaṭipanno viharasi sāmīcippaṭipanno "
"anudhammacārī, samādāya taṃ dhammaṃ vattasī’ti."
msgstr ""
"And you practice in line with that teaching, you practice following that "
"procedure, you live in line with the teaching. You proceed having undertaken "
"that teaching.’"

msgctxt "dn29:10.5"
msgid ""
"Iti kho, cunda, satthāpi tattha gārayho, dhammopi tattha gārayho, sāvakopi "
"tattha evaṃ gārayho."
msgstr ""
"In such a case the teacher, the teaching, and the disciple are all to blame."

msgctxt "dn29:10.6"
msgid "Yo kho, cunda, evarūpaṃ sāvakaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Suppose someone was to say to such a disciple:"

msgctxt "dn29:10.7"
msgid "‘addhāyasmā ñāyappaṭipanno ñāyamārādhessatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Clearly the venerable is practicing following the method and will succeed "
"in completing that method.’"

msgctxt "dn29:10.8"
msgid ""
"Yo ca pasaṃsati, yañca pasaṃsati, yo ca pasaṃsito bhiyyoso mattāya vīriyaṃ "
"ārabhati."
msgstr ""
"The one who praises, the one who they praise, and the one who, being "
"praised, rouses up even more energy all make much bad karma."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn29:10.9"
msgid "Sabbe te bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavanti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:10.10"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn29:10.11"
msgid ""
"Evañhetaṃ, cunda, hoti durakkhāte dhammavinaye duppavedite aniyyānike "
"anupasamasaṃvattanike asammāsambuddhappavedite."
msgstr ""
