msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "dn29:13.11"
msgid ""
"Evañhetaṃ, cunda, hoti svākkhāte dhammavinaye suppavedite niyyānike "
"upasamasaṃvattanike sammāsambuddhappavedite."
msgstr ""
"It’s because that teaching and training is well explained and well "
"propounded, emancipating, leading to peace, announced by someone who is a "
"fully awakened Buddha."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:14.1"
msgid "3. Sāvakānutappasatthu"
msgstr "When Disciples Have Regrets"

# Comm: aviññāpitatthāti abodhitatthā. I think this is a mistake. it is to be understood in line with the Buddha inviting the monks to question him on his deathbed. viññāpita is used in the sense "asked about or for".
#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wp" id="wp10"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.122"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn29:15.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, cunda, satthā ca loke udapādi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, dhammo ca "
"svākkhāto suppavedito niyyāniko upasamasaṃvattaniko sammāsambuddhappavedito, "
"aviññāpitatthā cassa honti sāvakā saddhamme, na ca tesaṃ kevalaṃ paripūraṃ "
"brahmacariyaṃ āvikataṃ hoti uttānīkataṃ sabbasaṅgāhapadakataṃ "
"sappāṭihīrakataṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Take the case where a teacher arises in the world who is perfected, a fully "
"awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained and well propounded, "
"emancipating, leading to peace, announced by someone who is fully awakened. "
"But the disciples haven’t inquired about the meaning of that good teaching. "
"And the spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure has not been "
"disclosed and revealed to them with all its collected sayings, with its "
"demonstrable basis, well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans."

msgctxt "dn29:15.2"
msgid "Atha nesaṃ satthuno antaradhānaṃ hoti."
msgstr "And then their teacher passes away."

msgctxt "dn29:15.3"
msgid "Evarūpo kho, cunda, satthā sāvakānaṃ kālaṅkato anutappo hoti."
msgstr ""
"When such a teacher has passed away the disciples are tormented with regret."

msgctxt "dn29:15.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn29:15.5"
msgid ""
"‘Satthā ca no loke udapādi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, dhammo ca svākkhāto "
"suppavedito niyyāniko upasamasaṃvattaniko sammāsambuddhappavedito, "
"aviññāpitatthā camha saddhamme, na ca no kevalaṃ paripūraṃ brahmacariyaṃ "
"āvikataṃ hoti uttānīkataṃ sabbasaṅgāhapadakataṃ sappāṭihīrakataṃ yāva "
"devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They think: ‘Our teacher was perfected, a fully awakened Buddha. His "
"teaching was well explained, but we didn’t inquire about the meaning, and "
"the spiritual practice was not fully disclosed to us."

msgctxt "dn29:15.6"
msgid "Atha no satthuno antaradhānaṃ hotī’ti."
msgstr "And then our teacher passed away.’"

msgctxt "dn29:15.7"
msgid "Evarūpo kho, cunda, satthā sāvakānaṃ kālaṅkato anutappo hoti."
msgstr ""
"When such a teacher has passed away the disciples are tormented by regrets."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:16.1"
msgid "4. Sāvakānanutappasatthu"
msgstr "When Disciples Have No Regrets"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wp" id="wp11"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.123"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:17.1"
msgid "Idha pana, cunda, satthā ca loke udapādi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho."
msgstr ""
"Take the case where a teacher arises in the world who is perfected, a fully "
"awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "dn29:17.2"
msgid ""
"Dhammo ca svākkhāto suppavedito niyyāniko upasamasaṃvattaniko "
"sammāsambuddhappavedito."
msgstr ""
"The teaching is well explained and well propounded, emancipating, leading to "
"peace, announced by someone who is fully awakened. "

msgctxt "dn29:17.3"
msgid ""
"Viññāpitatthā cassa honti sāvakā saddhamme, kevalañca tesaṃ paripūraṃ "
"brahmacariyaṃ āvikataṃ hoti uttānīkataṃ sabbasaṅgāhapadakataṃ "
"sappāṭihīrakataṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The disciples have inquired about the meaning of that good teaching. And the "
"spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure has been disclosed and "
"revealed to them with all its collected sayings, with its demonstrable "
"basis, well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans."

msgctxt "dn29:17.4"
msgid "Atha nesaṃ satthuno antaradhānaṃ hoti."
msgstr "And then their teacher passes away."

msgctxt "dn29:17.5"
msgid "Evarūpo kho, cunda, satthā sāvakānaṃ kālaṅkato ananutappo hoti."
msgstr "When such a teacher has passed away the disciples are free of regrets."

msgctxt "dn29:17.6"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn29:17.7"
msgid "‘Satthā ca no loke udapādi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho."
msgstr "They think: ‘Our teacher was perfected, a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "dn29:17.8"
msgid ""
"Dhammo ca svākkhāto suppavedito niyyāniko upasamasaṃvattaniko "
"sammāsambuddhappavedito."
msgstr "His teaching was well explained, "

msgctxt "dn29:17.9"
msgid ""
"Viññāpitatthā camha saddhamme, kevalañca no paripūraṃ brahmacariyaṃ āvikataṃ "
"hoti uttānīkataṃ sabbasaṅgāhapadakataṃ sappāṭihīrakataṃ yāva devamanussehi "
"suppakāsitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"we inquired about the meaning, and the spiritual practice was fully "
"disclosed to us."

msgctxt "dn29:17.10"
msgid "Atha no satthuno antaradhānaṃ hotī’ti."
msgstr "And then our teacher passed away.’"

msgctxt "dn29:17.11"
msgid "Evarūpo kho, cunda, satthā sāvakānaṃ kālaṅkato ananutappo hoti."
msgstr "When such a teacher has passed away the disciples are free of regrets."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:18.1"
msgid "5. Brahmacariyaaparipūrādikathā"
msgstr "On the Incomplete Spiritual Path, Etc."

# Both RD and MW seem to take this as referring to a monk. But it refers to the Buddha, as is made clear in the recapitulation.
#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wp" id="wp12"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:19.1"
msgid ""
"Etehi cepi, cunda, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brahmacariyaṃ hoti, no ca kho satthā "
"hoti thero rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto."
msgstr ""
"Now suppose, Cunda, that a spiritual path possesses those factors. But the "
"teacher is not senior, long standing, long gone forth, advanced in years, "
"and reached the final stage of life."

msgctxt "dn29:19.2"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ hoti tenaṅgena."
msgstr "Then that spiritual path is incomplete in that respect."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wp" id="wp13"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:20.1"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho, cunda, etehi ceva aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brahmacariyaṃ hoti, "
"satthā ca hoti thero rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto."
msgstr ""
"But when a spiritual path possesses those factors and the teacher is senior,"

msgctxt "dn29:20.2"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ hoti tenaṅgena."
msgstr "then that spiritual path is complete in that respect."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wp" id="wp14"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:21.1"
msgid ""
"Etehi cepi, cunda, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brahmacariyaṃ hoti, satthā ca hoti "
"thero rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto, no ca khvassa therā "
"bhikkhū sāvakā honti viyattā vinītā visāradā pattayogakkhemā."
msgstr ""
"Now suppose that a spiritual path possesses those factors and the teacher is "
"senior. But there are no senior monk disciples who are competent, educated, "
"assured, have attained sanctuary,"

msgctxt "dn29:21.2"
msgid ""
"Alaṃ samakkhātuṃ saddhammassa, alaṃ uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammehi "
"suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"who can rightly explain the true teaching, and who can can legitimately and "
"completely refute the doctrines of others that come up, and teach with a "
"demonstrable basis."

msgctxt "dn29:21.3"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ hoti tenaṅgena."
msgstr "Then that spiritual path is incomplete in that respect."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wp" id="wp15"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:22.1"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho, cunda, etehi ceva aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brahmacariyaṃ hoti, "
"satthā ca hoti thero rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto, therā "
"cassa bhikkhū sāvakā honti viyattā vinītā visāradā pattayogakkhemā."
msgstr ""
"But when a spiritual path possesses those factors and the teacher is senior "
"and there are competent senior monks,"

msgctxt "dn29:22.2"
msgid ""
"Alaṃ samakkhātuṃ saddhammassa, alaṃ uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammehi "
"suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desetuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:22.3"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ hoti tenaṅgena."
msgstr "then that spiritual path is complete in that respect."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wp" id="wp16"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.124"></a>
