"‘lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso, ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ "
"sabrahmacāriṃ passāma evaṃ atthupetaṃ byañjanupetan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate to see a venerable such as "
"yourself, so well-versed in the meaning and the phrasing, as one of our "
"spiritual companions!’"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:36.1"
msgid "8. Paccayānuññātakāraṇa"
msgstr "The Reasons for Allowing Requisites"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wp" id="wp27"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.130"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:37.1"
msgid ""
"Na vo ahaṃ, cunda, diṭṭhadhammikānaṃyeva āsavānaṃ saṃvarāya dhammaṃ desemi."
msgstr ""
"Cunda, I do not teach you solely for restraining defilements that affect the "
"present life."

msgctxt "dn29:37.2"
msgid ""
"Na panāhaṃ, cunda, samparāyikānaṃyeva āsavānaṃ paṭighātāya dhammaṃ desemi."
msgstr ""
"Nor do I teach solely for protecting against defilements that affect lives "
"to come."

msgctxt "dn29:37.3"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammikānaṃ cevāhaṃ, cunda, āsavānaṃ saṃvarāya dhammaṃ desemi;"
msgstr ""
"I teach both for restraining defilements that affect the present life and"

#. VAR: ca → cāti (bahūsu)
msgctxt "dn29:37.4"
msgid "samparāyikānañca āsavānaṃ paṭighātāya."
msgstr "protecting against defilements that affect lives to come."

# Both MW and RD have optative mod here, but it is not justified.
msgctxt "dn29:37.5"
msgid "Tasmātiha, cunda, yaṃ vo mayā cīvaraṃ anuññātaṃ, alaṃ vo taṃ—"
msgstr "And that’s why I have allowed robes for you that suffice"

msgctxt "dn29:37.6"
msgid ""
"yāvadeva sītassa paṭighātāya, uṇhassa paṭighātāya, "
"ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ paṭighātāya, yāvadeva "
"hirikopīnapaṭicchādanatthaṃ."
msgstr ""
"only for the sake of warding off cold, heat, hunger, and thirst; for warding "
"off the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles; and for "
"covering the private parts."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn29:37.7"
msgid ""
"Yo vo mayā piṇḍapāto anuññāto, alaṃ vo so yāvadeva imassa kāyassa ṭhitiyā "
"yāpanāya vihiṃsūparatiyā brahmacariyānuggahāya, iti purāṇañca vedanaṃ "
"paṭihaṅkhāmi, navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi, yātrā ca me bhavissati "
"anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro ca."
msgstr ""
"I have allowed alms-food for you that suffices, not for fun, indulgence, "
"adornment, or decoration, but only to continue and sustain this body, avoid "
"harm, and support spiritual practice; so that you will put an end to old "
"discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and will keep on living "
"blamelessly and at ease."

msgctxt "dn29:37.8"
msgid "Yaṃ vo mayā senāsanaṃ anuññātaṃ, alaṃ vo taṃ—"
msgstr "I have allowed lodgings for you that suffice "

msgctxt "dn29:37.9"
msgid ""
"yāvadeva sītassa paṭighātāya, uṇhassa paṭighātāya, "
"ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ paṭighātāya, yāvadeva "
"utuparissayavinodanapaṭisallānārāmatthaṃ."
msgstr ""
"only for the sake of warding off cold, heat, hunger, and thirst; for warding "
"off the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles; and to shelter "
"from harsh weather and enjoy retreat."

msgctxt "dn29:37.10"
msgid ""
"Yo vo mayā gilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhāro anuññāto, alaṃ vo so yāvadeva "
"uppannānaṃ veyyābādhikānaṃ vedanānaṃ paṭighātāya abyāpajjaparamatāya."
msgstr ""
"I have allowed medicines and supplies for the sick for you that suffice only "
"for the sake of warding off the pains of illness and to promote good health."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:38.1"
msgid "9. Sukhallikānuyoga"
msgstr "Indulgence in Pleasure"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="wp" id="wp28"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:39.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say:"

msgctxt "dn29:39.2"
msgid "‘sukhallikānuyogamanuyuttā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā viharantī’ti."
msgstr "‘The ascetics who follow the Sakyan live indulging in pleasure.’"

#. VAR: Evaṃvādino → ... vadamānā (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn29:39.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā:"
msgstr "You should say to them: "

msgctxt "dn29:39.4"
msgid "‘katamo so, āvuso, sukhallikānuyogo?"
msgstr "‘What is that indulgence in pleasure?"

msgctxt "dn29:39.5"
msgid "Sukhallikānuyogā hi bahū anekavihitā nānappakārakā’ti."
msgstr "For there are many different kinds of indulgence in pleasure.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="wp" id="wp29"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:40.1"
msgid ""
"Cattārome, cunda, sukhallikānuyogā hīnā gammā pothujjanikā anariyā "
"anatthasaṃhitā na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na "
"abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"These four kinds of indulgence in pleasure, Cunda, are low, crass, ordinary, "
"ignoble, and pointless. They don’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, "
"cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

msgctxt "dn29:40.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four? "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="wp" id="wp30"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:41.1"
msgid "Idha, cunda, ekacco bālo pāṇe vadhitvā vadhitvā attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when some fool makes themselves happy and pleased by killing living "
"creatures."

msgctxt "dn29:41.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo sukhallikānuyogo."
msgstr "This is the first kind of indulgence in pleasure."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="wp" id="wp31"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.131"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:42.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, cunda, idhekacco adinnaṃ ādiyitvā ādiyitvā attānaṃ sukheti "
"pīṇeti."
msgstr "Furthermore, someone makes themselves happy and pleased by theft."

msgctxt "dn29:42.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyo sukhallikānuyogo."
msgstr "This is the second kind of indulgence in pleasure."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="wp" id="wp32"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:43.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, cunda, idhekacco musā bhaṇitvā bhaṇitvā attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti."
msgstr "Furthermore, someone makes themselves happy and pleased by lying."

msgctxt "dn29:43.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyo sukhallikānuyogo."
msgstr "This is the third kind of indulgence in pleasure."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="wp" id="wp33"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:44.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, cunda, idhekacco pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto "
"paricāreti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, someone amuses themselves, supplied and provided with the five "
"kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "dn29:44.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho sukhallikānuyogo."
msgstr "This is the fourth kind of indulgence in pleasure."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="wp" id="wp34"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:45.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, cunda, cattāro sukhallikānuyogā hīnā gammā pothujjanikā anariyā "
"anatthasaṃhitā na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na "
"abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"These are the four kinds of indulgence in pleasure that are low, crass, "
"ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. They don’t lead to disillusionment, "
"dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a><a class="wp" id="wp35"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:46.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say:"

# RD and MW phrase this as a question, which is unjustified.
msgctxt "dn29:46.2"
msgid ""
"‘ime cattāro sukhallikānuyoge anuyuttā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā viharantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetics who follow the Sakyan live indulging in pleasure in these four "
"ways.’"

#. VAR: vo → te (pts1)
msgctxt "dn29:46.3"
msgid "Te vo ‘mā hevaṃ’ tissu vacanīyā."
msgstr "They should be told, ‘Not so!’"

msgctxt "dn29:46.4"
msgid "Na te vo sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ, abbhācikkheyyuṃ asatā abhūtena."
msgstr ""
"It isn’t right to say that about you; it misrepresents you with an untruth."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="wp" id="wp36"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:47.1"
msgid ""
"Cattārome, cunda, sukhallikānuyogā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya "
"upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"These four kinds of indulgence in pleasure, when developed and cultivated, "
"lead solely to disillusionment, fading away, cessation, peace, insight, "
"awakening, and extinguishment."

msgctxt "dn29:47.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a><a class="wp" id="wp37"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:48.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, cunda, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ "
"savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unwholesome qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected. "

msgctxt "dn29:48.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo sukhallikānuyogo."
msgstr "This is the first kind of indulgence in pleasure."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="wp" id="wp38"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:49.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, cunda, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are "
"stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption. It has the "
"rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, "
"and unification of mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "dn29:49.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:49.3"
msgid "dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:49.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyo sukhallikānuyogo."
msgstr "This is the second kind of indulgence in pleasure."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a><a class="wp" id="wp39"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:50.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, cunda, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains "
"in the third absorption. They meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, "
"personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss’. "

msgctxt "dn29:50.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:50.3"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:50.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyo sukhallikānuyogo."
msgstr "This is the third kind of indulgence in pleasure."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a><a class="wp" id="wp40"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.132"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:51.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, cunda, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and "
"sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption. It is "
"without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. "

msgctxt "dn29:51.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:51.3"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:51.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho sukhallikānuyogo."
msgstr "This is the fourth kind of indulgence in pleasure."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a><a class="wp" id="wp41"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:52.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, cunda, cattāro sukhallikānuyogā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya "
"upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"These are the four kinds of indulgence in pleasure which, when developed and "
"cultivated, lead solely to disillusionment, fading away, cessation, peace, "
"insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a><a class="wp" id="wp42"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:53.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say:"

msgctxt "dn29:53.2"
msgid ""
"‘ime cattāro sukhallikānuyoge anuyuttā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā viharantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetics who follow the Sakyan live indulging in pleasure in these four "
"ways.’"

msgctxt "dn29:53.3"
msgid "Te vo ‘evaṃ’ tissu vacanīyā."
msgstr "They should be told, ‘Exactly so!’"

msgctxt "dn29:53.4"
msgid "Sammā te vo vadamānā vadeyyuṃ, na te vo abbhācikkheyyuṃ asatā abhūtena."
msgstr ""
"It’s right to say that about you; it doesn’t misrepresent you with an "
"untruth."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:54.1"
msgid "10. Sukhallikānuyogānisaṃsa"
msgstr "The Benefits of Indulgence in Pleasure"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a><a class="wp" id="wp43"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:55.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say:"

msgctxt "dn29:55.2"
msgid ""
"‘ime panāvuso, cattāro sukhallikānuyoge anuyuttānaṃ viharataṃ kati phalāni "
"katānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"“How many fruits and benefits may be expected by those who live indulging in "
"pleasure in these four ways?”"

msgctxt "dn29:55.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā:"
msgstr "You should say to them:"

msgctxt "dn29:55.4"
msgid ""
"‘ime kho, āvuso, cattāro sukhallikānuyoge anuyuttānaṃ viharataṃ cattāri "
"phalāni cattāro ānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā."
msgstr ""
"‘Four benefits may be expected by those who live indulging in pleasure in "
"these four ways."

msgctxt "dn29:55.5"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "dn29:55.6"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpanno hoti "
"avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, with the ending of three fetters a mendicant becomes a stream-"
"enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.  "

msgctxt "dn29:55.7"
msgid "Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ phalaṃ, paṭhamo ānisaṃso."
msgstr "This is the first fruit and benefit."

msgctxt "dn29:55.8"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ "
"tanuttā sakadāgāmī hoti, sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karoti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant—with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening "
"of greed, hate, and delusion—becomes a once-returner. They come back to this "
"world once only, then make an end of suffering."

msgctxt "dn29:55.9"
msgid "Idaṃ dutiyaṃ phalaṃ, dutiyo ānisaṃso."
msgstr "This is the second fruit and benefit."

msgctxt "dn29:55.10"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"parikkhayā opapātiko hoti, tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, with the ending of the five lower fetters, a mendicant is "
"reborn spontaneously and will become extinguished there, not liable to "
"return from that world."

msgctxt "dn29:55.11"
msgid "Idaṃ tatiyaṃ phalaṃ, tatiyo ānisaṃso."
msgstr "This is the third fruit and benefit."

msgctxt "dn29:55.12"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ "
"paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom "
"by wisdom in this very life, and lives having achieved it with their own "
"insight due to the end of defilements."

msgctxt "dn29:55.13"
msgid "Idaṃ catutthaṃ phalaṃ catuttho ānisaṃso."
msgstr "This is the fourth fruit and benefit."

msgctxt "dn29:55.14"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, āvuso, cattāro sukhallikānuyoge anuyuttānaṃ viharataṃ imāni cattāri "
"phalāni, cattāro ānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā’ti."
msgstr ""
"These four benefits may be expected by those who live indulging in pleasure "
"in these four ways.’"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:56.1"
msgid "11. Khīṇāsavaabhabbaṭhāna"
msgstr "Things Impossible for the Perfected"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a><a class="wp" id="wp44"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.133"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:57.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say:"

# Both RD and MW take dhamma in (at)thitadhamma here as "doctrine", but it is at AN 8.19 in the same context, but of the ocean, where it just means "stable". Both places are glossed as ṭhitasabhāvā. Incidentally, the context here shows that PTS dict's "eternal" for AN 8.19 is wrong.
msgctxt "dn29:57.2"
msgid "‘aṭṭhitadhammā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā viharantī’ti."
msgstr "‘The ascetics who follow the Sakyan are inconsistent.’"

msgctxt "dn29:57.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā:"
msgstr "You should say to them:"

msgctxt "dn29:57.4"
msgid ""
"‘atthi kho, āvuso, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena "
"sāvakānaṃ dhammā desitā paññattā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyā."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, these things have been taught and pointed out for his disciples "
"by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully "
"awakened Buddha, not to be transgressed so long as life lasts."

msgctxt "dn29:57.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, indakhīlo vā ayokhīlo vā gambhīranemo sunikhāto acalo "
"asampavedhī;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a boundary pillar or an iron pillar with deep foundations, "
"firmly embedded, immovable and unshakable."

msgctxt "dn29:57.6"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, āvuso, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena "
"sāvakānaṃ dhammā desitā paññattā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyā."
msgstr ""
"In the same, these things have been taught and pointed out for his disciples "
"by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully "
"awakened Buddha, not to be transgressed so long as life lasts."

msgctxt "dn29:57.7"
msgid ""
"Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro "
"anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, abhabbo so "
"nava ṭhānāni ajjhācarituṃ."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, who has lived the "
"spiritual life, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved "
"their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed "
"through final knowledge—can’t transgress in nine respects."

msgctxt "dn29:57.8"
msgid "Abhabbo, āvuso, khīṇāsavo bhikkhu sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropetuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with defilements ended can’t deliberately take the life of a "
"living creature, take something with the intention to steal, have sex, tell "
"a deliberate lie, or store up goods for their own enjoyment like they did as "
"a lay person. And they can’t make decisions prejudiced by favoritism, "
"hostility, stupidity, or cowardice."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn29:57.9"
msgid "abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyituṃ;"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:57.10"
msgid "abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevituṃ;"
