msgctxt "dn29:57.12"
msgid ""
"abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu sannidhikārakaṃ kāme paribhuñjituṃ, seyyathāpi "
"pubbe āgārikabhūto;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:57.13"
msgid "abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu chandāgatiṃ gantuṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:57.14"
msgid "abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu dosāgatiṃ gantuṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:57.15"
msgid "abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu mohāgatiṃ gantuṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:57.16"
msgid "abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu bhayāgatiṃ gantuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:57.17"
msgid ""
"Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro "
"anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, abhabbo so "
"imāni nava ṭhānāni ajjhācaritun’ti."
msgstr "A mendicant who is perfected can’t transgress in these nine respects.’"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:58.1"
msgid "12. Pañhābyākaraṇa"
msgstr "Questions and Answers"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a><a class="wp" id="wp45"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.134"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:59.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say:"

msgctxt "dn29:59.2"
msgid ""
"‘atītaṃ kho addhānaṃ ārabbha samaṇo gotamo atīrakaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paññapeti, "
"no ca kho anāgataṃ addhānaṃ ārabbha atīrakaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paññapeti, tayidaṃ "
"kiṃsu tayidaṃ kathaṃsū’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama demonstrates boundless knowledge and vision of the past, "
"but not of the future. What’s up with that?’"

msgctxt "dn29:59.3"
msgid ""
"Te ca aññatitthiyā paribbājakā aññavihitakena ñāṇadassanena aññavihitakaṃ "
"ñāṇadassanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ maññanti yathariva bālā abyattā."
msgstr ""
"Those wanderers, like incompetent fools, seem to imagine that one kind of "
"knowledge and vision can be demonstrated by means of another kind of "
"knowledge and vision."

msgctxt "dn29:59.4"
msgid "Atītaṃ kho, cunda, addhānaṃ ārabbha tathāgatassa satānusāriñāṇaṃ hoti;"
msgstr ""
"Regarding the past, the Realized One has knowledge stemming from memory."

msgctxt "dn29:59.5"
msgid "so yāvatakaṃ ākaṅkhati tāvatakaṃ anussarati."
msgstr "He recollects as far as he wants."

msgctxt "dn29:59.6"
msgid "Anāgatañca kho addhānaṃ ārabbha tathāgatassa bodhijaṃ ñāṇaṃ uppajjati:"
msgstr ""
"Regarding the future, the Realized One has the knowledge born of awakening:"

msgctxt "dn29:59.7"
msgid "‘ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’ti."
msgstr "‘This is my last birth. Now there are no more future lives.’"

msgctxt "dn29:59.8"
msgid ""
"Atītañcepi, cunda, hoti abhūtaṃ atacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na taṃ tathāgato "
"byākaroti."
msgstr ""
"If a question about the past is untrue, false, and pointless, the Realized "
"One does not reply."

msgctxt "dn29:59.9"
msgid ""
"Atītañcepi, cunda, hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, tampi tathāgato na "
"byākaroti."
msgstr ""
"If a question about the past is true and substantive, but pointless, he does "
"not reply."

msgctxt "dn29:59.10"
msgid ""
"Atītañcepi, cunda, hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ, tatra kālaññū "
"tathāgato hoti tassa pañhassa veyyākaraṇāya."
msgstr ""
"If a question about the past is true, substantive, and beneficial, he knows "
"the right time to reply."

msgctxt "dn29:59.11"
msgid ""
"Anāgatañcepi, cunda, hoti abhūtaṃ atacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na taṃ tathāgato "
"byākaroti …"
msgstr ""
"And the Realized One replies to questions about the future or the present in "
"the same way."

msgctxt "dn29:59.12"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:59.13"
msgid "tassa pañhassa veyyākaraṇāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:59.14"
msgid ""
"Paccuppannañcepi, cunda, hoti abhūtaṃ atacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na taṃ "
"tathāgato byākaroti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:59.15"
msgid ""
"Paccuppannañcepi, cunda, hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, tampi "
"tathāgato na byākaroti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:59.16"
msgid ""
"Paccuppannañcepi, cunda, hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ, tatra kālaññū "
"tathāgato hoti tassa pañhassa veyyākaraṇāya."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a><a class="wp" id="wp46"></a>
#. VAR: tathāgato kālavādī → kālavādī saccavādī (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn29:60.1"
msgid ""
"Iti kho, cunda, atītānāgatapaccuppannesu dhammesu tathāgato kālavādī "
"bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"And so the Realized One has speech that’s well-timed, true, meaningful, in "
"line with the teaching and training. That’s why he’s called the ‘Realized "
"One’."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn29:60.2"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho, cunda, sadevakassa lokassa samārakassa sabrahmakassa "
"sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ "
"pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, sabbaṃ tathāgatena abhisambuddhaṃ, "
"tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"In this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its "
"ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—whatever is seen, heard, thought, "
"cognized, searched, and explored by the mind, all that has been understood "
"by a Realized One. That’s why he’s called the ‘Realized One’."

msgctxt "dn29:60.3"
msgid ""
"Yañca, cunda, rattiṃ tathāgato anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambujjhati, "
"yañca rattiṃ anupādisesāya nibbānadhātuyā parinibbāyati, yaṃ etasmiṃ antare "
"bhāsati lapati niddisati."
msgstr ""
"From the night when a Realized One understands the supreme perfect awakening "
"until the night he becomes fully extinguished—through the natural principle "
"of extinguishment, without anything left over—everything he speaks, says, "
"and expresses is real, not otherwise."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn29:60.4"
msgid "Sabbaṃ taṃ tatheva hoti no aññathā, tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati."
msgstr "That’s why he’s called the ‘Realized One’."

msgctxt "dn29:60.5"
msgid "Yathāvādī, cunda, tathāgato tathākārī, yathākārī tathāvādī."
msgstr "The Realized One does as he says, and says as he does."

msgctxt "dn29:60.6"
msgid ""
"Iti yathāvādī tathākārī, yathākārī tathāvādī, tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati."
msgstr "Since this is so, that’s why he’s called the ‘Realized One’."

msgctxt "dn29:60.7"
msgid ""
"Sadevake loke, cunda, samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya "
