#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="51"></a><a class="wp" id="wp51"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:66.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "The wanderers might say:"

msgctxt "dn29:66.2"
msgid "‘kasmā panetaṃ, āvuso, samaṇena gotamena abyākatan’ti?"
msgstr "‘But why has this not been declared by the ascetic Gotama?’"

msgctxt "dn29:66.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā:"
msgstr "You should say to them:"

msgctxt "dn29:66.4"
msgid ""
"‘na hetaṃ, āvuso, atthasaṃhitaṃ na dhammasaṃhitaṃ na ādibrahmacariyakaṃ na "
"nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya "
"na nibbānāya saṃvattati, tasmā taṃ bhagavatā abyākatan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Because it’s not beneficial or relevant to the fundamentals of the "
"spiritual life. It doesn’t lead to disillusionment, fading away, cessation, "
"peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. That’s why it hasn’t been "
"declared by the Buddha.’"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:67.1"
msgid "14. Byākataṭṭhāna"
msgstr "The Declared Points"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="52"></a><a class="wp" id="wp52"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:68.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say:"

msgctxt "dn29:68.2"
msgid "‘kiṃ panāvuso, samaṇena gotamena byākatan’ti?"
msgstr "‘But what has been declared by the ascetic Gotama?’"

msgctxt "dn29:68.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā:"
msgstr "You should say to them:"

msgctxt "dn29:68.4"
msgid ""
"‘idaṃ dukkhanti kho, āvuso, bhagavatā byākataṃ, ayaṃ dukkhasamudayoti kho, "
"āvuso, bhagavatā byākataṃ, ayaṃ dukkhanirodhoti kho, āvuso, bhagavatā "
"byākataṃ, ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadāti kho, āvuso, bhagavatā "
"byākatan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘What has been declared by the Buddha is this: “This is suffering”—“This is "
"the origin of suffering”—“This is the cessation of suffering”—“This is the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="53"></a><a class="wp" id="wp53"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.137"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:69.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ "
"vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "The wanderers might say:"

msgctxt "dn29:69.2"
msgid "‘kasmā panetaṃ, āvuso, samaṇena gotamena byākatan’ti?"
msgstr "‘But why has this been declared by the ascetic Gotama?’"

msgctxt "dn29:69.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā:"
msgstr "You should say to them:"

msgctxt "dn29:69.4"
msgid ""
"‘etañhi, āvuso, atthasaṃhitaṃ, etaṃ dhammasaṃhitaṃ, etaṃ ādibrahmacariyakaṃ "
"ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya "
"saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"‘Because it’s beneficial and relevant to the fundamentals of the spiritual "
"life. It leads to disillusionment, fading away, cessation, peace, insight, "
"awakening, and extinguishment."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn29:69.5"
msgid "Tasmā taṃ bhagavatā byākatan’ti."
msgstr "That’s why it has been declared by the Buddha.’"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:70.1"
msgid "15. Pubbantasahagatadiṭṭhinissaya"
msgstr "Views of the Past"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="54"></a><a class="wp" id="wp54"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.138"></a>
#. VAR: vo → te (s2, s3)
msgctxt "dn29:71.1"
msgid ""
"Yepi te, cunda, pubbantasahagatā diṭṭhinissayā, tepi vo mayā byākatā, yathā "
"te byākātabbā."
msgstr ""
"Cunda, I have explained to you as they should be explained the views that "
"some rely on regarding the past."

#. VAR: tathā → tattha (bj, s1-3, mr)
