#. no ahaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn29:71.2"
msgid "Yathā ca te na byākātabbā, kiṃ vo ahaṃ te tathā byākarissāmi?"
msgstr "Shall I explain them to you in the wrong way?"

msgctxt "dn29:71.3"
msgid ""
"Yepi te, cunda, aparantasahagatā diṭṭhinissayā, tepi vo mayā byākatā, yathā "
"te byākātabbā."
msgstr ""
"I have explained to you as they should be explained the views that some rely "
"on regarding the future."

msgctxt "dn29:71.4"
msgid "Yathā ca te na byākātabbā, kiṃ vo ahaṃ te tathā byākarissāmi?"
msgstr "Shall I explain them to you in the wrong way?"

msgctxt "dn29:71.5"
msgid ""
"Katame ca te, cunda, pubbantasahagatā diṭṭhinissayā, ye vo mayā byākatā, "
"yathā te byākātabbā."
msgstr "What are the views that some rely on regarding the past?"

msgctxt "dn29:71.6"
msgid "Yathā ca te na byākātabbā, kiṃ vo ahaṃ te tathā byākarissāmi?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:71.7"
msgid "Santi kho, cunda, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "dn29:71.8"
msgid "‘sassato attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The self and the cosmos are eternal. This is the only truth, everything "
"else is wrong.’"

msgctxt "dn29:71.9"
msgid "Santi pana, cunda, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "dn29:71.10"
msgid "‘asassato attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are not eternal,"

msgctxt "dn29:71.11"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:71.12"
msgid "sassato ca asassato ca attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or both eternal and not eternal,"

msgctxt "dn29:71.13"
msgid "neva sassato nāsassato attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or neither eternal nor not eternal."

msgctxt "dn29:71.14"
msgid "sayaṃkato attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "The self and the cosmos are made by oneself,"

msgctxt "dn29:71.15"
msgid "paraṃkato attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or made by another,"

msgctxt "dn29:71.16"
msgid "sayaṃkato ca paraṃkato ca attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or made by both oneself and another,"

msgctxt "dn29:71.17"
msgid ""
"asayaṅkāro aparaṅkāro adhiccasamuppanno attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti."
msgstr "or they have arisen by chance, not made by oneself or another."

msgctxt "dn29:71.18"
msgid "‘Sassataṃ sukhadukkhaṃ …"
msgstr "Pleasure and pain are eternal,"

msgctxt "dn29:71.19"
msgid "asassataṃ sukhadukkhaṃ …"
msgstr "or not eternal,"

msgctxt "dn29:71.20"
msgid "sassatañca asassatañca sukhadukkhaṃ …"
msgstr "or both eternal and not eternal,"

msgctxt "dn29:71.21"
msgid "nevasassataṃ nāsassataṃ sukhadukkhaṃ …"
msgstr "or neither eternal nor not eternal."

msgctxt "dn29:71.22"
msgid "sayaṃkataṃ sukhadukkhaṃ …"
msgstr "Pleasure and pain are made by oneself,"

msgctxt "dn29:71.23"
msgid "paraṃkataṃ sukhadukkhaṃ …"
msgstr "or made by another,"

msgctxt "dn29:71.24"
msgid "sayaṃkatañca paraṃkatañca sukhadukkhaṃ …"
msgstr "or made by both oneself and another,"

msgctxt "dn29:71.25"
msgid ""
"asayaṃkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti."
msgstr ""
"or they have arisen by chance, not made by oneself or another. This is the "
"only truth, everything else is wrong.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="55"></a><a class="wp" id="wp55"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:72.1"
msgid "Tatra, cunda, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "Regarding this, I go up to the ascetics and brahmins whose view is that"

msgctxt "dn29:72.2"
msgid "‘sassato attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti."
msgstr "the self and the cosmos are eternal,"

msgctxt "dn29:72.3"
msgid "Tyāhaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "and say:"

msgctxt "dn29:72.4"
msgid "‘atthi nu kho idaṃ, āvuso, vuccati:"
msgstr "‘Reverends, is this what you say:"

msgctxt "dn29:72.5"
msgid "“sassato attā ca loko cā”’ti?"
msgstr "“The self and the cosmos are eternal”?’"

msgctxt "dn29:72.6"
msgid "Yañca kho te evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "But when they said ‘Yes!"

msgctxt "dn29:72.7"
msgid "‘idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti."
msgstr "This is the only truth, everything else is wrong,’"

msgctxt "dn29:72.8"
msgid "Taṃ tesaṃ nānujānāmi."
msgstr "I don’t acknowledge that."

msgctxt "dn29:72.9"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn29:72.10"
msgid "Aññathāsaññinopi hettha, cunda, santeke sattā."
msgstr "Because there are beings who have different opinions on this topic."

msgctxt "dn29:72.11"
msgid ""
"Imāyapi kho ahaṃ, cunda, paññattiyā neva attanā samasamaṃ samanupassāmi kuto "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"I don’t see any such expositions that are equal to my own, still less "
"superior."

msgctxt "dn29:72.12"
msgid "Atha kho ahameva tattha bhiyyo yadidaṃ adhipaññatti."
msgstr ""
"Rather, I am the one who is superior when it comes to the higher exposition."

