msgid "Yathā ca te na byākātabbā, kiṃ vo ahaṃ te tathā byākarissāmi?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:75.3"
msgid "Santi, cunda, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "dn29:75.4"
msgid "‘rūpī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti."
msgstr "‘The self is physical and sound after death,"

msgctxt "dn29:75.5"
msgid "Santi pana, cunda, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:75.6"
msgid "‘arūpī attā hoti …"
msgstr "or it is non-physical,"

msgctxt "dn29:75.7"
msgid "rūpī ca arūpī ca attā hoti …"
msgstr "or both physical and non-physical,"

msgctxt "dn29:75.8"
msgid "nevarūpī nārūpī attā hoti …"
msgstr "or neither physical nor non-physical,"

msgctxt "dn29:75.9"
msgid "saññī attā hoti …"
msgstr "or percipient,"

msgctxt "dn29:75.10"
msgid "asaññī attā hoti …"
msgstr "or non-percipient,"

msgctxt "dn29:75.11"
msgid "nevasaññīnāsaññī attā hoti …"
msgstr "or neither percipient nor non-percipient,"

msgctxt "dn29:75.12"
msgid ""
"attā ucchijjati vinassati na hoti paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti."
msgstr ""
"or the self is annihilated and destroyed when the body breaks up, and doesn’"
"t exist after death. This is the only truth, everything else is wrong.’"

msgctxt "dn29:75.13"
msgid "Tatra, cunda, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "Regarding this, I go up to the ascetics and brahmins whose view is that"

msgctxt "dn29:75.14"
msgid "‘rūpī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti."
msgstr "the self is physical and sound after death,"

msgctxt "dn29:75.15"
msgid "Tyāhaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "and say:"

msgctxt "dn29:75.16"
msgid "‘atthi nu kho idaṃ, āvuso, vuccati:"
msgstr "‘Reverends, is this what you say:"

msgctxt "dn29:75.17"
msgid "“rūpī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā”’ti?"
msgstr "“The self is physical and sound after death”?’"

msgctxt "dn29:75.18"
msgid "Yañca kho te evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "But when they said ‘Yes!"

msgctxt "dn29:75.19"
msgid "‘idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti."
msgstr "This is the only truth, other ideas are stupid,’"

msgctxt "dn29:75.20"
msgid "Taṃ tesaṃ nānujānāmi."
msgstr "I don’t acknowledge that."

msgctxt "dn29:75.21"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn29:75.22"
msgid "Aññathāsaññinopi hettha, cunda, santeke sattā."
msgstr "Because there are beings who have different opinions on this topic."

msgctxt "dn29:75.23"
msgid ""
"Imāyapi kho ahaṃ, cunda, paññattiyā neva attanā samasamaṃ samanupassāmi kuto "
"bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"I don’t see any such expositions that are equal to my own, still less "
"superior."

msgctxt "dn29:75.24"
msgid "Atha kho ahameva tattha bhiyyo yadidaṃ adhipaññatti."
msgstr ""
"Rather, I am the one who is superior when it comes to the higher exposition."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="58"></a><a class="wp" id="wp58"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.141"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:76.1"
msgid "Tatra, cunda, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr ""
"Regarding this, I go up to the ascetics and brahmins who advocate all the "
"other views as described above."

msgctxt "dn29:76.2"
msgid "‘arūpī attā hoti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:76.3"
msgid "rūpī ca arūpī ca attā hoti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:76.4"
msgid "nevarūpīnārūpī attā hoti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:76.5"
msgid "saññī attā hoti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:76.6"
msgid "asaññī attā hoti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:76.7"
msgid "nevasaññīnāsaññī attā hoti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:76.8"
msgid ""
"attā ucchijjati vinassati na hoti paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:76.9"
msgid "Tyāhaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:76.10"
msgid "‘atthi nu kho idaṃ, āvuso, vuccati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:76.11"
msgid "“attā ucchijjati vinassati na hoti paraṃ maraṇā”’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:76.12"
msgid "Yañca kho te, cunda, evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:76.13"
msgid "‘idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:76.14"
msgid "Taṃ tesaṃ nānujānāmi."
msgstr "And in each case, I don’t acknowledge that."

msgctxt "dn29:76.15"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn29:76.16"
msgid "Aññathāsaññinopi hettha, cunda, santeke sattā."
msgstr "Because there are beings who have different opinions on this topic."

msgctxt "dn29:76.17"
msgid ""
"Imāyapi kho ahaṃ, cunda, paññattiyā neva attanā samasamaṃ samanupassāmi, "
"kuto bhiyyo."
msgstr ""
"I don’t see any such expositions that are equal to my own, still less "
"superior."

msgctxt "dn29:76.18"
msgid "Atha kho ahameva tattha bhiyyo yadidaṃ adhipaññatti."
msgstr ""
"Rather, I am the one who is superior when it comes to the higher exposition."

msgctxt "dn29:76.19"
msgid ""
"Ime kho te, cunda, aparantasahagatā diṭṭhinissayā, ye vo mayā byākatā, yathā "
"te byākātabbā."
msgstr ""
"These are the views that some rely on regarding the future, which I have "
"explained to you as they should be explained."

#. VAR: byākarissāmi → byākarissāmīti (bj, c1)
msgctxt "dn29:76.20"
msgid "Yathā ca te na byākātabbā, kiṃ vo ahaṃ te tathā byākarissāmi?"
msgstr "Shall I explain them to you in the wrong way?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="59"></a><a class="wp" id="wp59"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:77.1"
msgid ""
"Imesañca, cunda, pubbantasahagatānaṃ diṭṭhinissayānaṃ imesañca "
"aparantasahagatānaṃ diṭṭhinissayānaṃ pahānāya samatikkamāya evaṃ mayā "
"cattāro satipaṭṭhānā desitā paññattā."
msgstr ""
"I have taught and pointed out the four kinds of mindfulness meditation for "
"giving up and going beyond all these views of the past and the future."

msgctxt "dn29:77.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "dn29:77.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, cunda, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body, keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "dn29:77.4"
msgid "Vedanāsu vedanānupassī …"
msgstr "They meditate by observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "dn29:77.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:77.6"
msgid "citte cittānupassī …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "dn29:77.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn29:77.8"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles, keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world. "

msgctxt "dn29:77.9"
msgid ""
"Imesañca, cunda, pubbantasahagatānaṃ diṭṭhinissayānaṃ imesañca "
"aparantasahagatānaṃ diṭṭhinissayānaṃ pahānāya samatikkamāya."
msgstr ""
"These are the four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I have taught for "
"giving up and going beyond all these views of the past and the future."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn29:77.10"
msgid "Evaṃ mayā ime cattāro satipaṭṭhānā desitā paññattā”ti."
msgstr " "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="60"></a><a class="wp" id="wp60"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:78.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upavāṇo bhagavato piṭṭhito ṭhito hoti "
"bhagavantaṃ bījayamāno."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Upavāṇa was standing behind the Buddha fanning "
"him."

msgctxt "dn29:78.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upavāṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "He said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn29:78.3"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "dn29:78.4"
msgid "Pāsādiko vatāyaṃ, bhante, dhammapariyāyo;"
msgstr "This exposition of the teaching is impressive, sir,"

msgctxt "dn29:78.5"
msgid ""
"supāsādiko vatāyaṃ, bhante, dhammapariyāyo, ko nāmāyaṃ, bhante, "
"dhammapariyāyo”ti?"
msgstr ""
"it is very impressive. Sir, what is the name of this exposition of the "
"teaching?”"

msgctxt "dn29:78.6"
msgid ""
"“Tasmātiha tvaṃ, upavāṇa, imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ ‘pāsādiko’ tveva naṃ "
"dhārehī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Well, Upavāṇa, you may remember this exposition of the teaching as ‘The "
"Impressive Discourse’.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="61"></a><a class="wp" id="wp61"></a>
msgctxt "dn29:79.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "This is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn29:79.2"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā upavāṇo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti."
msgstr "Uplifted, Venerable Upavāṇa approved of what the Buddha said. "

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn29:80.1"
msgid "Pāsādikasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
